Patch Set 2:

> Hi Andreas,
 > I just found if we changed "struct lprocfs_stats *obd_memory" to
 > "struct percpu_counter *obd_memory", then all of the lprocfs_*
 > operations on obd_memory in obdclass_init() need to be changed to
 > use percpu_counter_* functions. I'm not sure if there is a proper
 > way to change the following one:
 > 
 > lprocfs_counter_init(obd_memory, OBD_MEMORY_STAT,
 > LPROCFS_CNTR_AVGMINMAX | LPROCFS_TYPE_BYTES,
 > "memused");

The percpu_counter is allocated statically 

 struct percpu_counter obd_memory;
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(obd_memory);

then to initialize this memory before use:

 #ifdef HAVE_PERCPU_COUNTER_INIT_GFP_FLAG
        rc = percpu_counter_init(&obd_memory, 0, GFP_KERNEL);
 #else
        rc = return percpu_counter_init(&obd_memory, 0);
 #endif
        if (rc < 0) {
                CERROR("obdclass: initializing 'obd_memory' failed: rc = %d\n", rc);
                return rc;

and to free it later:

         percpu_counter_destroy(&obd_memory);                   

We might want to make a wrapper for percpu_counter_init() if
